ational history that interfaces with the sophisticated existing body of scholarship on early Soviet history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4a20th century. 4aBolsheviks. 4aEurope. 4aEuropean history. 4aSoviet Union. 4aUnion of Soviet Socialist Republics (USSR). 4acivil war. 4ahistory. 4arevolution. 4awar. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Eastern.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520915671?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520915671423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520915671/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles